	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 10th 6:49 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am level 30 and I do not think that I know the fullest extent of the cleric class.<br><br>I never find myself 'overworked.' I am nearly ALWAYS with a secondary healer or because there are so many Druids and a lot of Paladins. I was once in a group with two warriors and a shadowknight and me, the cleric. It was extremely fun and I had to heal very little. Most of the time I just locked down the monster with Stuns.<br><br>All of our quests? I agree with you on that fact, that we have no low level quests. But NO ONE has any CLASS SPECIFIC low level quests. If you are referring to generic quests, then I disagree with you. Crushbone and Deathfist belts provide GREAT experience.<br><br>As to buying armor, EVERY class has to do that. I have only bought TWO sets of armor, one Leather set that cost me about 25 pp and SOME bronze, namely the Breastplate, Arms, Legs, Hands, Feet, and Helm, which altogether probably cost me 80 pp. Bronze weighs a lot and you do not tank that much, so I simply leave the other slots either leather or WIS-enhancing items.<br><br>About money? EVERY class is poor until level 16-17. We might 'have it worse', but we can, as Gedran said, wear PLATE armor. We don't 'have' to buy it, but we have the OPTION and we should EVENTUALLY.<br><br>On making money, simply twiddle your thumbs for a few more levels. If you really need cash then go to an orc camp in EC or the WC one and just sit there for four hours. I guarantee that you will make around 100 pp at least because you will get about 50 DF belts which go for 2 pp each (or 4-5 if you are selling to an idiot :)<br><br>When you are level 16-17, then simply go to HighPass Hold and get in that orc group. You loot bronze weapons ALL THE TIME that sell for 2-4 pp. I must have made 350 pp there.<br><br>Clerics rock at soloing undead, but soloing is VERY boring because we have to solo wizard-style. If you want to have FUN and get good loot, then GROUP.<br><br>I would suggest you go to the chessboard in Butcherblock until level 12. At 12, go and camp Skeleton Lrodd in Befallen until 13. At 13 park yourself at Derv 2 in North Ro and wait for four hours for that DING. At 14, stay in the derv group for a bubble of exp. Then go to the Estate of Unrest through Butcherblock and Dagnor's Cauldron. Stay there, kill Death Beetles and the Undead until level 16. At 16 go to HighPass and stay there until 21. At 21 go to the Lake of Ill Omen and stay there until 29, where you should go to Cazic Thule or another dungeon like Solusek A. That is where I am now. Clerics DO NOT SUCK :)<br><br>Update: From 28-31 I have been in Crypt of Dalnir, Icy orcs in Everfrost, Permafrost king room, and Highkeep. My suggestion is Highkeep, for there is a bank, merchants, and guards close to the combat area.<br><br>In a typical battle with an enchanter and two tanks, we typically pull 2-3 sarnaks in Lake of Ill Omen.<br><br>If 2 sarnaks, then chanter mezzes one, I Stun/Holy Might/med/etc. Whenever a tank drops to 2 bubbles of health I cast Greater Heal on them to bring them to FULL. Yes, FULL. For only one bubble of mana, I heal 3 bubs of HP on a twinked Ogre Warrior at my level.<br><br>If 3 sarnaks are pulled, tanks will hit one, I will hit the other with melee UNTIL the enchanter can get a Mez off. At that point I INSTANTLY stop attacking, back up, and continue stunning/healing.<br><br>My point is that clerics are an EXTREMELY powerful class, and I am ALWAYS needed in groups.<br><br>-Mendin Woonds, 30 High Elven Cleric<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
